&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CLINICAL FELLOW POSTS &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;INTENSIVE CARE MEDICINE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Applicants are invited to apply for Clinical Fellow Posts in the Departments of Anaesthetics and Critical Care at The Lewisham and Greenwich NHS Trust. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The work would be centred at Queen Elizabeth Hospital, Woolwich to start in October 2020 for a period of 6 to 12 months with the possibility to amend if required. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alongside the Trainees, Clinical Fellows are eligible for study leave with a supporting budget to accommodate CPD.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Queen Elizabeth Hospital (QEH) is located on Stadium Road and is well served by public transport: bus and rail. Charlton, Woolwich Dockyard and Woolwich Arsenal are only a short bus ride away from the hospital. All stations are a short journey from London terminals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants may also have the opportunity to do 6 months in the following specialties’:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Obstetric Anaesthesia.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Anaesthesia&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Critical Care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information regarding these posts please e-mail Toni [Critical Care Rota Coordinator] via e-mail: a.gillies@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
